        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 3:08PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Castleberry, or 9 miles south of Evergreen, moving southwest at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Castleberry, East Brewton, and Brewton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
